text: Duhaga of Bunyoro was Omukama of Bunyoro (1731-c.1782). Omukama of Bunyoro is the name given to rulers of the central African kingdom of Bunyoro-Kitara. Duhaga was preceded by Olimi III - (c. 1710-1731) and later succeeded by Olimi IV - (c. 1782-1786). ==References== Category:Bunyoro Category:Ugandan monarchies Category:1731 births Category:1782 deaths
